Joseph P. Brennan III won the 2020 election but was not sworn in. SMD 4B05 is vacant as of Feb. 24, 2021.

The 2020 election in 7B03 ended in a tie between two write-in candidates: Lindsey Botts and Walter Leroy Peacock III. The tie was broken by a drawing of names from a pot by DCBOE, and Lindsey Botts won the drawing.
David L. Retland won a tiebreaker in a special election on May 26, 2022 for the vacant seat, defeating Jamaal Pearsall. Both candidates received 15 votes and Retland won in the drawing of lots.
A special election was held in June 2021 and Joel Gastn was the winner. DCist: I May Be Incarcerated, But My Voice Still Matters.: Resident At D.C. Jail Wins Local Election
